'''細胞記憶'''，亦作'''身體記憶'''（Body memory）是一個[[偽科學|偽科學]]假說，認為人體本身或身體上的所有細胞均有儲存記憶<ref name=skepdic>{{cite web | url = http://skepdic.com/cellular.html | title = Cellular Memory | publisher = [[The_Skeptic's_Dictionary|The Skeptic's Dictionary]] | date = 2009-02-23 | accessdate = 2010-09-23 | last = Carroll | first = RT | authorlink = Robert Todd Carroll | language = en | archive-date = 2018-10-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181008181830/http://skepdic.com/cellular.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>或[[個性特質|個性特質]]<ref name=theophanes>{{cite web |url=http://theophanes.hubpages.com/hub/Cellular-Memories-in-Organ-Transplant-Recipients |title=Inherited Memory in Organ Transplant Recipients |trans_title=器官移殖接受者所承繼的記憶 |language=en |date=2013-01-25 |accessdate=2013-07-12 |archive-date=2015-10-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151013072324/http://theophanes.hubpages.com/hub/Cellular-Memories-in-Organ-Transplant-Recipients |dead-url=no }}</ref>的能力，而不是主流學說所認為的只存在於[[大脑|大腦]]。這個假說可用來解釋某些腦部並未有用來儲存某種記憶的特定條件，而透過[[釋放記憶|釋放記憶]]的方式來重新恢復，例如：{{link-en|幻肢痛|Phantom pain}}，又或[[器官移植|器官移殖]]後的'''殘存記憶'''<ref name=skepdic />。這個假說亦被認為可以用來解釋[[智能|智能]]的起源<ref name=nature>{{cite journal |url=http://www.nature.com/news/2008/080123/full/451385a.html |title=Cellular memory hints at the origins of intelligence |journal=[[自然雜誌|Nature]] |date=2008-01-23 |accessdate=2013-07-12 |language=en |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112001631/https://www.nature.com/news/2008/080123/full/451385a.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，以及一些透過身體感知而重新喚醒被抑壓的[[亂倫|亂倫]]或[[性虐待|性虐待]]的回憶的現象<ref name = "Smith">{{cite journal | url = http://www.ipt-forensics.com/journal/volume5/j5_4_2.htm | title = Body Memories: And Other Pseudo-Scientific Notions of "Survivor Psychology"  | journal = Issues in Child Abuse Accusations | volume = 5 | issue = 4 | year = 1993 | last = Smith | first = SE | access-date = 2013-07-11 | archive-date = 2018-10-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181002015837/http://www.ipt-forensics.com/journal/volume5/j5_4_2.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。這個假說之所以被認為是偽科學，是因為現時並未有確切證據去指明大腦以外的其他身體組織有儲存記憶的能力<ref name ="Smith"/><ref name = "Lilienfeld">{{Cite book |editor= Scott O. Lilienfeld SO; Lynn SJ; Lohr JM | title=Science and Pseudoscience in Clinical Psychology |trans_title=臨床心理學的科學與偽科學 |year = 2002|publisher=The Guilford Press|isbn=1-57230-828-1 }}</ref>。

==歷史==
有關以大腦以外的器官作記憶的假說，可以追遡至19世紀法国作家{{link-en|莫里斯·雷纳德|Maurice Renard}}的恐怖科幻小說《{{link-fr|奧拉克之手|Les Mains d'Orlac}}》<ref name=theophanes />，講述一位鋼琴家因為意外而失去雙手，後來獲得移殖另一對手，卻不知道這對手是來自一位謀殺犯的。這小說隨後多次被改編成為電影。

==懷疑論==

1993年，一位心理學家蘇珊·史密斯（Susan E. Smith）在一篇第一次在[[假记忆体综合征|假记忆体综合征]]的[[學術會議|學術會議]]上發表的論文，把「細胞記憶」跟「[[倖存者心理學|倖存者心理學]]」兩者相關連起來，指出：
{{quote|body memories are thought to literally be emotional, kinesthetic, or chemical recordings stored at the cellular level and retrievable by returning to or recreating the chemical, emotional, or kinesthetic conditions under which the memory recordings are filed.  She wrote in the abstract of the paper that "one of the most commonly used theories to support the ideology of [[repressed_memories|repressed memories]] or incest and sexual abuse amnesia is body memories." <ref name="Smith"/>}}
{{cquote|身體的記憶從字面上被認為是在細胞層面上的情緒、動覺、或化學紀錄存儲，並能透過重現該記憶存儲時的化學、情緒與動覺條件提取。她在論文的提要寫到：「其中一個最常用來支持『記憶壓抑』與『亂倫與性虐待記憶喪失』意識的理論就是身體記憶。」}}

史密斯繼續表明自己的立場接著說：

{{quote|The belief in these pseudoscientific concepts appears to be related to scientific illiteracy, gullibility, and a lack of critical thinking skills and reasoning abilities in both the mental health community and in society at large.<ref name="Smith"/>}}
{{cquote|這些偽科學概念的信念貌似與精神健康業界和社會整體的科學文盲、愚蠢、以及缺乏批判思考技巧與推理能力有關。}}

